\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
DNA has the form of a double helix.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
The 2 complementary strands of DNA are sequences of nucleotides that carry
 1 of 4 possible nitrogen-containing bases.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Base pairing is a specific hydrogen bond between 1 purine and 1 pyrimidine:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
adenine (A) will always bind thymine (T), and cytosine (C) will always bind
 guanine (G).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
These bonds maintain DNA in the double-helix structure that is widely known.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_inset


\begin_inset Box Frameless
