\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
The genome is packed and organized in structures called chromosomes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Most animals inherit 1 chromosome from each parent and are called diploids
 (i.e.
 they have 1 homologous pair of chromosomes).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Some animals, and many plants, have multiple homologous pairs of chromosomes
 and are defined as polyploid.
 .
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 0.5cm
\end_inset


