\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
For each gene, diploid individuals will each have two alleles.
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Alleles are alternative forms of the same gene that can differ in 1 or more
 variations in the 4 bases A, G, C, or T.
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Alleles create diversity.
\begin_inset VSpace 0.2cm
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
The combination of these alleles is what defines a genotype for an individual
 organism 
\end_layout

\end_inset


