\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Most of genome is the same for most individuals (same species):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
There are some positions in which there is variability, called:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Polymorphisms, or
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
DNA variations.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Many polymorphisms are neutral, and likely have no phenotypic effect
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
However, some are at the basis of what differentiates one individual from
 the other.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 0.5cm
\end_inset


