\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
Selection for breeding has historically been made using estimated breeding
 values (EBV), without identifying genes involved in phenotypes.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size scriptsize
EBVs were simply estimated from the study of pedigrees and phenotypic records
 with the knowledge of the heritability of each trait
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 0.5cm
